        <!-- Primary Research Project Section -->
        <section id="research" class="py-5 py-md-5 bg-light">
            <div class="container">
                <h2 class="section-heading text-center">Featured Research: 2019 Rio Grande Birth Cohort</h2>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-lg-7">
                        <h3 class="h4 fw-bold text-primary mb-3">Project Overview</h3>
                        <p class="lead">This is a fixed, prospective, population-based cohort study designed to investigate the life course epidemiology of mental health and its intergenerational transmission in a middle-income country setting.</p>
                        <p>The study includes **2,051 mothers and their infants** born in Rio Grande in 2019, providing a unique and culturally-specific dataset that differentiates us from traditional cohorts.</p>

                        <h3 class="h4 fw-bold text-primary mt-4 mb-3">Key Findings & Subprojects</h3>
                        <div class="card p-3 mb-3 border-warning border-3">
                            <p class="mb-1 fw-bold">Impact of COVID-19:</p>
                            <p class="card-text">We found a significant increase in maternal mental health problems during the COVID-19 pandemic, reporting a **six-fold increase in depressive symptoms** and a **three-fold increase in anxiety** compared to baseline.</p>
                        </div>
                        <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                            <li class="list-group-item bg-light"><i class="fa-solid fa-mobile-screen-button me-2 text-primary"></i>**AI-Powered Interaction Analysis:** Using wearable cameras and AI facial recognition to analyze mother-child interactions.</li>
                            <li class="list-group-item bg-light"><i class="fa-solid fa-water me-2 text-primary"></i>**Disaster Epidemiology:** Evaluating the effects of the 2024 floods in Rio Grande do Sul on maternal and child mental health.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-5 mt-4 mt-lg-0">
                        <h3 class="h4 fw-bold text-primary mb-3">Key International Collaborators</h3>
                        <ul class="list-group shadow-sm">
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                                <span class="fw-bold">Rebecca Pearson</span>
                                <br><small>Manchester Metropolitan University (MMU). Expert in observational and computational methods.</small>
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                                <span class="fw-bold">Ana Luiza Goncalves Soares</span>
                                <br><small>University of Bristol. Expert in life course epidemiology and advanced longitudinal analyses.</small>
                            </li>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                                <span class="fw-bold">Marc Bornstein</span>
                                <br><small>National Institute of Child Health and Human Development. Expert in child development and family studies.</small>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Impact & Vision (KPIs) Section -->
        <section id="impact" class="py-5 py-md-5">
            <div class="container">
                <h2 class="section-heading text-center">Measuring Success: Impact & Long-Term Vision</h2>
                <div class="row text-center g-4">
                    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
                        <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded shadow-sm h-100">
                            <div class="kpi-icon mb-3"><i class="fa-solid fa-book-open"></i></div>
                            <h3 class="h5 fw-bold text-primary">Publications (Quality Priority)</h3>
                            <p class="mb-0">Success measured by the **number and quality** of scientific publications, with a strong emphasis on publishing in high-impact factor journals. Our priority is **quality over quantity**.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
                        <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded shadow-sm h-100">
                            <div class="kpi-icon mb-3"><i class="fa-solid fa-sack-dollar"></i></div>
                            <h3 class="h5 fw-bold text-primary">Targeted Funding</h3>
                            <p class="mb-0">Targeting national grants from **CNPq** and international funding from organizations like **Wellcome**. The long-term vision is to secure funding to make research the primary job for all members.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
                        <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded shadow-sm h-100">
                            <div class="kpi-icon mb-3"><i class="fa-solid fa-graduation-cap"></i></div>
                            <h3 class="h5 fw-bold text-primary">Future KPI: Capacity Building</h3>
                            <p class="mb-0">Developing a formal system to track the professional growth of our early-career researchers, including conference presentations and successful thesis completion.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
                        <div class="p-4 bg-white rounded shadow-sm h-100">
                            <div class="kpi-icon mb-3"><i class="fa-solid fa-hand-holding-heart"></i></div>
                            <h3 class="h5 fw-bold text-primary">Future KPI: Social Impact</h3>
                            <p class="mb-0">Implementing a system to track media appearances and community presentations to ensure our scientific knowledge is translated into broadly accessible formats for the public good.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row mt-5">
